\begin{align*}
2(a + b + c) &= 140\\
\sqrt{a^2 + b^2 + c^2} &= 21
\end{align*}
and we want the value of $2(ab + bc + ca)$. With some algebraic manipulation, we get
\begin{align*}
ab + bc + ca &= \frac{(140/2)^2 - a^2 - b^2 - c^2}{2}\\
&= \frac{4900 - (a^2 + b^2 + c^2)}{2}\\
&= \frac{4900 - 21^2}{2} = 1105.
\end{align*}
Therefore, the total surface area of the box is $2(ab + bc + ca) = \boxed{2210}$. </think> <answer>2210</answer>

