n &\equiv 1 \pmod{4} \\
n &\equiv 1 \pmod{5}
\end{align*}
To find the solution, we can use the Chinese Remainder Theorem or simply guess and check numbers that satisfy these conditions. The smallest number that satisfies all three conditions is $n = 61$.
